# Print Partner Non-Commercial Software License

## TLDR

- **Run Print Partner** on your own machines for personal, hobby, academic, or other non-commercial use — including organizing STL kits, manifests, and exports for your shop or club.
- **Commercial print farms and print businesses** may use Print Partner **internally** to run a 3D printing operation (plate planning, checkoff, manifests, etc.) when you sell **printed parts or services** — no separate commercial license required for that internal use.
- **Study and modify** the source code for non-commercial use. Share your changes **share-alike**: recipients must get this same license and required notices.
- **Fork or redistribute?** Include a copy of this license, [ATTRIBUTION.md](ATTRIBUTION.md), and visible credit to Chad Lynch / Print Partner. Do not imply endorsement without permission.
- **Sell the software?** (installers, paid downloads, SaaS, bundling in a product you sell, etc.) You need **written permission** from Chad Lynch — see [COMMERCIAL.md](COMMERCIAL.md).
- **Sell printed parts?** Yes. This license applies to the **software**, not the physical parts you print.
- **Warranty:** The software is provided **as is** with no warranty. Use at your own risk; back up important data.

